<quiz>
    <question>
        <prompt>The German reparations crisis affected the U.S. economy by:</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Strengthening international trade</option>
            <option letter="b">Contributing to international banking failures</option>
            <option letter="c">Boosting American exports</option>
            <option letter="d">Increasing foreign investment</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>Germany's inability to pay World War I reparations in the early 1930s contributed to international banking failures. When Germany defaulted on payments, it triggered bank failures in Austria and Germany that spread to other European banks. This banking crisis affected American banks that had made loans to European nations, contributing to the international financial crisis and deepening the Great Depression.</explanation>
    </question>
</quiz>
